     <h2>
      Welcome
     </h2>
     <!-- <p>This website is intended to inform interested parties about the progress made implementing<a href ="http://www.leg.state.co.us/clics/clics2012a/csl.nsf/fsbillcont3/305CE972C8F2F51D8725798400602A21?open&file=1278_enr.pdf"> HB 12-1278</a>, an act authorizing the study of the South Platte River alluvial aquifer.
        In it you will find guidance for finding information about the <a href="./study.shtml">Study</a>; the <a href="./physical.html">Physical</a> setting of the South Platte River Basin ; the <a href="./history.html">Historical</a> background of South Platte River Basin surface and groundwater use; <a href="./resources.html">Resource</a> material for in depth study and research; ways to provide <a href="./input.html">Input</a> to the study; <a href="./findings.html">Findings</a> as the Study progresses, News and Events; and ways to <a href="./contact.html">Contact Us</a>.
        To learn more about the individual sections click on the word describing the topic of interest to you.
        We are excited to be a part of the effort toward solutions of South Platte River Basin groundwater issues as we at the Colorado Water Institute, with your help, move forward. </p>
        <img src="img/Irrigated_Lands_2010.png" alt="South Platte" align="middle" />-->
     <p>
      In 2012, the Colorado Legislature passed
      <a href="http://www.leg.state.co.us/clics/clics2012a/csl.nsf/fsbillcont3/305CE972C8F2F51D8725798400602A21?open&amp;file=1278_enr.pdf" target="_blank">
       HB 12-1278
      </a>
      , which commissions a study of the interaction of the South Platte alluvial aquifer by the
      <a href="http://cwi.colostate.edu" target="_blank">
       Colorado Water Institute
      </a>
      at Colorado State University.
     </p>
     <p>
      This website was created by the
      <i>
       Colorado Water Institute
      </i>
      to keep interested parties informed on the products, processes and actions taken as the study unfolded.
     </p>
     <img align="left" alt="Location of the South Platte River basin showing extent of mapped alluvium and distribution of alluvial wells" src="img/SP_BasinSmall.png" style="padding:0 15px 0 15px;"/>
     <p>
      In this website, you will find information about:
     </p>
